{"type":"message","id":"4c7f2e90","parentId":"e4ae8c77","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:09:32.842Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"MediaCrawler MCP needs aiomysql (MySQL), but MEMORY.md says it uses json storage mode (no MySQL needed). Let me check the main.py to see if there's a way to run it without MySQL.\n\nActually, let me re-read the MEMORY.md more carefully. It says \"存储模式：json（不需要 MySQL）\". But the db.py imports aiomysql. Maybe the script has a way to bypass MySQL?\n\nLet me check the main.py to understand the architecture. Actually, let me just try to install aiomysql or find another way to get the小红书 content.\n \nThe小红书 push script relies on the小红书 MCP at port 18080, but that's the MediaCrawler MCP which needs MySQL. I could try using the older小红书 MCP at port 18060 instead, or maybe there's a simpler approach here. Let me look at the xiaohongshu_push_v3.py to understand what it's actually trying to do."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ewlyqgz49o2t_1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":50,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\linkang\\.openclaw\\workspace\\xiaohongshu_push_v3.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775200163945}}
{"type":"message","id":"21dedcf9","parentId":"4c7f2e90","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:09:32.863Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ewlyqgz49o2t_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 小红书旅游推送 v3 - 带封面图版（cron直接调用版）\nimport requests, json, sys, os, time\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\nMCP_URL = 'http://localhost:18080/mcp'\nUPLOAD_DIR = r'C:\\Users\\linkang\\.openclaw\\workspace\\uploads'\nos.makedirs(UPLOAD_DIR, exist_ok=True)\n\ndef init_mcp():\n    s = requests.Session()\n    hdrs = {'Accept': 'application/json, text/event-stream'}\n    r1 = s.post(MCP_URL, json={\n        'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'id': 1, 'method': 'initialize',\n        'params': {'protocolVersion': '2024-11-05', 'capabilities': {},\n                   'clientInfo': {'name': 'openclaw', 'version': '1.0'}}\n    }, headers=hdrs, timeout=10)\n    hdrs['Mcp-Session-Id'] = r1.headers.get('Mcp-Session-Id', '')\n    s.post(MCP_URL, json={'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'method': 'notifications/initialized'}, headers=hdrs)\n    return s, hdrs\n\ndef call_mcp(s, hdrs, tool_name, arguments):\n    resp = s.post(MCP_URL, json={\n        'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'id': 99, 'method': 'tools/call',\n        'params': {'name': tool_name, 'arguments': arguments}\n    }, headers=hdrs, timeout=30)\n    return json.loads(resp.json()['result']['content'][0]['text'])\n\ndef get_travel_feeds(s, hdrs):\n    raw = call_mcp(s, hdrs, 'list_feeds', {})\n    feeds = raw.get('feeds', [])\n    \n    travel_kws = ['旅游', '旅行', '出游', '攻略', '打卡', '拍照', '度假', '景点', '风景', '春游', '踏青']\n    results = []\n    seen_ids = set()\n    \n    for f in feeds:\n        if f.get('modelType') != 'note':\n            continue\n        note_id = f.get('id', '')\n        if note_id in seen_ids:\n            continue\n        seen_ids.add(note_id)\n        \n        card = f.get('noteCard', {})\n        title = card.get('displayTitle', '')\n        if not any(kw in title for kw in travel_kws):\n            continue\n        \n        cover = card.get('cover', {})\n\n[140 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775200172855}}
