{"type":"message","id":"52e744f2","parentId":"8d1fd4c7","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:10:12.578Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Docker is not running at all. The docker daemon is not accessible. This explains why both cron jobs failed - the小红书 MCP needs Docker to run.\n\nThe user is asking why the cron jobs didn't send the messages. The answer is:\n1. Cron jobs failed with \"Delivering to Feishu requires target <chatId|user:openId|chat:chatId>\" - after gateway restart\n2. The underlying scripts also can't run because Docker is not running (for xiaohongshu MCP)\n\nI need to tell the user the truth: both cron tasks have been failing due to a Feishu delivery error and Docker not running. I should fix the Docker issue first.\n\n\nLooking at the error more carefully, the Feishu API error seems to stem from the cron job's delivery configuration having an unknown channel status rather than an actual API problem. The real blocker is that the script depends on the Docker-based xiaohongshu MCP which isn't currently accessible.\n\nI should check if there's an alternative way to reach the Feishu API directly instead of relying on that MCP, then notify the user about what needs to be resolved."},{"type":"text","text":"问题找到了，有两层：\n\n1. **Cron 任务投递 Feishu 失败** — 连续4次报错 `Delivering to Feishu requires target`，Gateway 重启后已恢复\n2. **MediaCrawler MCP（小红书）根本跑不起来** — Docker 桌面版没在运行，连不上 `npipe:////./pipe/dockerDesktopLinuxEngine`\n\n要手动触发两个推送的话，得先修 Docker。先帮你看下能不能启动：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_742zu3e9ubi7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"net start | findstr -i docker","timeout":8}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775200199427}}
