{"type":"message","id":"67912107","parentId":"5afb9e8c","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:11:58.595Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The xiaohongshu MCP is running on port 18060. But the script `xiaohongshu_push_v3.py` is connecting to port 18080. The script needs to be updated to use port 18060, OR the script should use the v2 API (old xiaohongshu MCP on port 18060).\n\nWait, looking at the MEMORY.md:\n- 小红书 MCP: port 18060 (Docker container)\n- MediaCrawler MCP: port 18080 (different MCP)\n\nSo there are two different MCPs:\n1. `xiaohongshu-mcp` Docker on port 18060 - uses old API (`search_notes`, `get_comments`, etc.)\n\n\n2. `media-crawler-mcp` on port 18080 - uses new API (`crawl_search`, etc.)\n\nThe script `xiaohongshu_push_v3.py` is trying to connect to port 18080 with the new API but it's calling the wrong port. Since the xiaohongshu-mcp container is already on 18060, I should just update the script to point to that port instead. But I need to verify whether the 18060 image supports the `list_feeds` and `search_feeds` methods that the script is trying to call.\n\nLooking at the v2.0.0 API docs, the available tools are `check_login_status`, `get_login_qrcode`, `search_feeds`, `list_feeds`, and `get_feed_detail` - but the script is using `list_feeds` on port 18080 when it should be using the 18060 endpoint instead."},{"type":"text","text":"端口写错了，脚本连 18080，实际小红书 MCP 在 18060。一行修复：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iuxxds9ubwx3_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\linkang\\.openclaw\\workspace\\xiaohongshu_push_v3.py","old_string":"MCP_URL = 'http://localhost:18080/mcp'","new_string":"MCP_URL = 'http://localhost:18060/mcp'"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775200306279}}
