{"type":"message","id":"3430e140","parentId":"f474b855","timestamp":"2026-04-03T07:27:21.786Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the script changes directory to `./docs` internally and the stop words file is missing. This is a MediaCrawler setup issue. \n\nLet me take a completely different approach. Instead of trying to fix the MediaCrawler MCP, let me use the小红书 MCP directly (port 18060) but with a longer timeout and the correct tool. \n\nActually, the issue with the 小红书 MCP was that `search_feeds` timed out. But `list_feeds` worked before (returned 0 items but didn't timeout). \n\nLet me think about what really works:\n1. 小红书 MCP on 18060: `check_login_status` works, `list_feeds` works (returns data), `search_feeds` times out\n\n\n2. MediaCrawler MCP: Can't start due to missing stopwords file\n\nThe real problem is that `search_feeds` takes longer than 30 seconds and times out. I could increase the timeout to 120 seconds and try again, or I could work with `list_feeds` since that actually returns results. Let me rewrite the推送 script to use `list_feeds` with a longer timeout and see if I can get it to work.\n\nActually, `list_feeds` is the recommended daily content approach, but it returned 0 items earlier. I think the issue is that I was filtering for travel keywords in the results—when I look at the raw `list_feeds` output, it returned an empty list, probably because the account isn't following travel creators or the feed is empty. I should test calling `list_feeds` directly and examine the actual response structure without any filtering."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fn2glwqpd2t8_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import requests, json, sys\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\n\nMCP_URL = 'http://localhost:18060/mcp'\ns = requests.Session()\nhdrs = {'Accept': 'application/json, text/event-stream'}\nr1 = s.post(MCP_URL, json={\n    'jsonrpc':'2.0','id':1,'method':'initialize',\n    'params':{'protocolVersion':'2024-11-05','capabilities':{},'clientInfo':{'name':'openclaw','version':'1.0'}}\n}, headers=hdrs, timeout=10)\nhdrs['Mcp-Session-Id'] = r1.headers.get('Mcp-Session-Id', '')\ns.post(MCP_URL, json={'jsonrpc':'2.0','method':'notifications/initialized'}, headers=hdrs)\n\n# Try list_feeds with longer timeout\nprint('Testing list_feeds...')\ntry:\n    resp = s.post(MCP_URL, json={\n        'jsonrpc':'2.0','id':2,'method':'tools/call',\n        'params':{'name':'list_feeds','arguments':{}}\n    }, headers=hdrs, timeout=60)\n    print('list_feeds status:', resp.status_code)\n    print('list_feeds response:', resp.text[:1000])\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print('list_feeds error:', e)\n\n# Try search_feeds with very long timeout\nprint('\\nTesting search_feeds...')\ntry:\n    resp = s.post(MCP_URL, json={\n        'jsonrpc':'2.0','id':3,'method':'tools/call',\n        'params':{'name':'search_feeds','arguments':{'keyword':'旅游'}}\n    }, headers=hdrs, timeout=120)\n    print('search_feeds status:', resp.status_code)\n    print('search_feeds response:', resp.text[:2000])\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print('search_feeds error:', e)\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\linkang\\.openclaw\\workspace\\test_xhs_tools.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775201219573}}
